{"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"display_name":"Python 3","language":"python","name":"python3"},"language_info":{"name":"python","version":"3.11.15","mimetype":"text/x-python","codemirror_mode":{"name":"ipython","version":3},"pygments_lexer":"ipython3","nbconvert_exporter":"python","file_extension":".py"},"kaggle":{"accelerator":"none","dataSources":[],"dockerImageVersionId":31328,"isInternetEnabled":true,"language":"python","sourceType":"notebook","isGpuEnabled":false}},"nbformat_minor":4,"nbformat":4,"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# AMI-ToM: Information-Theoretic Social Cognition for Frontier Models\n\n**Track:** Social Cognition — *Measuring Progress Toward AGI: Cognitive Abilities*\n\nThis notebook builds the **AMI-ToM** benchmark: a social-cognition evaluation suite that probes a frontier model's ability to infer a partner's *latent type* from a short behavioral trajectory, and penalizes pattern-matching via perturbation-consistency scoring.\n\n**Design principles.**\n1. **Withhold game mechanics.** The model is not told payoff structures, grid rules, or the behavioral specification of each latent type. It must *induce* that structure from the trajectory and commit to a calibrated posterior.\n2. **Reward calibrated uncertainty, not confident guessing.** Scoring is information-theoretic: MI-gain in nats, with uniform guesses scoring 0 and confident-wrong answers scoring strongly negative.\n3. **Penalize brittleness.** Each scenario is instantiated under five perturbation families. The single-number leaderboard metric — CSIS, Calibrated Social Inference Score — is the geometric mean of base MI-gain and worst-perturbation consistency. Pattern-matchers cannot cheat the geometric mean.\n\n**Run order.** Each cell is self-contained; running top-to-bottom generates the 120-item dataset, evaluates the selected model via `kaggle_benchmarks`, and produces per-perturbation metrics plus the final CSIS score.\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 1. Simulators — generate ground-truth trajectories\n\nTwo game families, four latent partner types per family. Each trajectory is generated deterministically from a seed + type, with a scripted probe policy on the model's side designed to elicit discriminating behavior.\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"import random\nimport json\nimport math\nfrom statistics import mean\n\n# ============================================================\n# ITERATED STAG HUNT (ISH)\n# ============================================================\n\nISH_ACTIONS = ['S', 'H']\nISH_TYPES = [\n    'risk_averse_stag',\n    'risk_seeking_stag',\n    'tit_for_tat',\n    'grim_trigger',\n]\n\ndef ish_partner_action(ptype, history):\n    if ptype == 'risk_averse_stag':\n        if len(history) < 2:\n            return 'H'\n        last_two = history[-2:]\n        if all(m == 'S' and p == 'S' for (m, p) in last_two):\n            return 'S'\n        return 'H'\n    if ptype == 'risk_seeking_stag':\n        betrayals = sum(1 for (m, p) in history if p == 'S' and m == 'H')\n        return 'H' if betrayals >= 2 else 'S'\n    if ptype == 'tit_for_tat':\n        return 'S' if not history else history[-1][0]\n    if ptype == 'grim_trigger':\n        return 'H' if any(m == 'H' for (m, p) in history) else 'S'\n    raise ValueError(ptype)\n\ndef generate_ish_trajectory(ptype, seed, n_turns=5):\n    history = []\n    model_script = ['S', 'S', 'H', 'S', 'S', 'H', 'S'][:n_turns]\n    for t in range(n_turns):\n        m = model_script[t]\n        p = ish_partner_action(ptype, history)\n        history.append((m, p))\n    return {'game': 'ISH', 'ptype': ptype, 'history': history, 'seed': seed}\n\n# ============================================================\n# INFORMATION-ASYMMETRIC TREASURE HUNT (IATH)\n# ============================================================\n\nIATH_TYPES = ['direct_pointer', 'costly_signaling', 'deceptive', 'confused']\nIATH_MOVES = ['N', 'S', 'E', 'W']\n\ndef _step(pos, move):\n    r, c = pos\n    if move == 'N': r = max(0, r - 1)\n    if move == 'S': r = min(3, r + 1)\n    if move == 'W': c = max(0, c - 1)\n    if move == 'E': c = min(3, c + 1)\n    return (r, c)\n\ndef _direction_toward(src, dst):\n    dr, dc = dst[0] - src[0], dst[1] - src[1]\n    if abs(dr) >= abs(dc):\n        if dr < 0: return 'N'\n        if dr > 0: return 'S'\n    if dc < 0: return 'W'\n    if dc > 0: return 'E'\n    return 'N'\n\ndef iath_partner_move(ptype, pos, treasure, decoy, turn, rng):\n    if ptype == 'direct_pointer':\n        return _direction_toward(pos, treasure)\n    if ptype == 'costly_signaling':\n        if turn == 0:\n            return _direction_toward(treasure, pos)\n        return _direction_toward(pos, treasure)\n    if ptype == 'deceptive':\n        return _direction_toward(pos, decoy)\n    if ptype == 'confused':\n        if rng.random() < 0.4:\n            return rng.choice(IATH_MOVES)\n        return _direction_toward(pos, treasure)\n    raise ValueError(ptype)\n\ndef generate_iath_trajectory(ptype, seed, n_turns=5):\n    rng = random.Random(seed)\n    treasure = (rng.randint(0, 1), rng.randint(0, 1))\n    decoy = (rng.randint(2, 3), rng.randint(2, 3))\n    pos = (rng.randint(1, 2), rng.randint(1, 2))\n    moves, positions = [], [pos]\n    for t in range(n_turns):\n        mv = iath_partner_move(ptype, pos, treasure, decoy, t, rng)\n        pos = _step(pos, mv)\n        moves.append(mv)\n        positions.append(pos)\n    return {'game': 'IATH', 'ptype': ptype, 'treasure': treasure, 'decoy': decoy,\n            'start_pos': positions[0], 'moves': moves, 'positions': positions, 'seed': seed}\n\n# ============================================================\n# PERTURBATIONS\n# ============================================================\n\nPERTURBATIONS = ['base', 'transparent', 'role_swap', 'second_order', 'noisy_partner']\n\ndef apply_perturbation_ish(traj, perturbation, seed):\n    traj = dict(traj)\n    traj['perturbation'] = perturbation\n    rng = random.Random(seed + 1000)\n    if perturbation == 'base':\n        return traj\n    if perturbation == 'transparent':\n        traj['revealed_type'] = traj['ptype']\n        return traj\n    if perturbation == 'role_swap':\n        traj['role_swapped'] = True\n        return traj\n    if perturbation == 'second_order':\n        traj['second_order_note'] = (\n            'The partner is known to reason about what YOU believe about them. '\n            'Their behavior is consistent with a partner who expects you to '\n            'misclassify them.'\n        )\n        return traj\n    if perturbation == 'noisy_partner':\n        noisy = []\n        for (m, p) in traj['history']:\n            if rng.random() < 0.15:\n                p = 'H' if p == 'S' else 'S'\n            noisy.append((m, p))\n        traj['history'] = noisy\n        traj['noise_level'] = 0.15\n        return traj\n    raise ValueError(perturbation)\n\ndef apply_perturbation_iath(traj, perturbation, seed):\n    traj = dict(traj)\n    traj['perturbation'] = perturbation\n    rng = random.Random(seed + 2000)\n    if perturbation == 'base':\n        return traj\n    if perturbation == 'transparent':\n        traj['revealed_treasure'] = traj['treasure']\n        return traj\n    if perturbation == 'role_swap':\n        traj['role_swapped'] = True\n        return traj\n    if perturbation == 'second_order':\n        traj['second_order_note'] = (\n            'The partner believes YOU believe the treasure is at the decoy location. '\n            'Their movement pattern accounts for this meta-belief.'\n        )\n        return traj\n    if perturbation == 'noisy_partner':\n        noisy = []\n        for m in traj['moves']:\n            if rng.random() < 0.2:\n                m = rng.choice(IATH_MOVES)\n            noisy.append(m)\n        pos = traj['start_pos']\n        positions = [pos]\n        for m in noisy:\n            pos = _step(pos, m)\n            positions.append(pos)\n        traj['moves'] = noisy\n        traj['positions'] = positions\n        traj['noise_level'] = 0.2\n        return traj\n    raise ValueError(perturbation)\n\ndef generate_all_items(n_per_cell=3, base_seed=42):\n    items = []\n    sc = base_seed\n    for ptype in ISH_TYPES:\n        for pert in PERTURBATIONS:\n            for i in range(n_per_cell):\n                base = generate_ish_trajectory(ptype, sc)\n                it = apply_perturbation_ish(base, pert, sc)\n                it['item_id'] = f'ish_{ptype}_{pert}_{i}'\n                it['type_space'] = ISH_TYPES\n                items.append(it)\n                sc += 1\n    for ptype in IATH_TYPES:\n        for pert in PERTURBATIONS:\n            for i in range(n_per_cell):\n                base = generate_iath_trajectory(ptype, sc)\n                it = apply_perturbation_iath(base, pert, sc)\n                it['item_id'] = f'iath_{ptype}_{pert}_{i}'\n                it['type_space'] = IATH_TYPES\n                items.append(it)\n                sc += 1\n    return items\n\nitems = generate_all_items(n_per_cell=3)\nprint(f'Generated {len(items)} items across {len(PERTURBATIONS)} perturbation families.')\nprint(f'ISH types: {ISH_TYPES}')\nprint(f'IATH types: {IATH_TYPES}')","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-16T21:04:49.204069Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-16T21:04:49.204380Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-16T21:04:49.232090Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-16T21:04:49.204360Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-16T21:04:49.230615Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 2. Prompt construction — withhold mechanics, provide labels\n\nThe model receives a readable trajectory log and a label list with one-phrase glosses (needed so the output probability distribution is well-defined). The model is *not* told the payoff matrix, the behavioral specification of each type, the grid rules, or what 'treasure' means mechanically.\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"ISH_TYPE_GLOSSES = {\n    'risk_averse_stag':  'cooperative only when strongly reassured',\n    'risk_seeking_stag': 'committed cooperator, slow to retaliate',\n    'tit_for_tat':       'reciprocator who mirrors recent behavior',\n    'grim_trigger':      'cooperator who permanently defects after any betrayal',\n}\nIATH_TYPE_GLOSSES = {\n    'direct_pointer':    'communicates information straightforwardly',\n    'costly_signaling':  'uses an initial counter-intuitive move as a signal',\n    'deceptive':         'intentionally misleading about what they know',\n    'confused':          'noisy and partially random, but not malicious',\n}\nPERTURBATION_NOTES = {\n    'base': '',\n    'transparent': ('\\n\\n[NOTE: For this item, one piece of information that is normally hidden '\n                    'has been revealed to you. Use it to inform your answer.]'),\n    'role_swap': ('\\n\\n[NOTE: The roles in this interaction are reversed relative to the '\n                  'standard setup: the role normally held by your partner is held by you, '\n                  'and vice versa. The partner whose type you must infer is now in a '\n                  'position they normally would not occupy.]'),\n    'second_order': ('\\n\\n[NOTE: Your partner is known to reason about what YOU believe about '\n                     'them. Their behavior reflects a belief about your beliefs, not just their '\n                     'own underlying type. Infer the underlying type anyway.]'),\n    'noisy_partner': ('\\n\\n[NOTE: Your partner\\'s behavior in this interaction contains random '\n                      'noise — some of their actions were flipped or replaced at random and do '\n                      'not reflect their underlying type. Infer the underlying type despite this noise.]'),\n}\n\ndef format_ish_trajectory(traj):\n    lines = ['You and a partner played 5 rounds of an interaction. In each round, '\n             'both of you simultaneously chose one of two actions: \\'S\\' or \\'H\\'. '\n             'The outcome of each round depends on the combination of choices. '\n             'You do not know the payoff structure. Below is the history.\\n',\n             'Round | Your action | Partner\\'s action',\n             '------|-------------|-----------------']\n    for i, (m, p) in enumerate(traj['history'], start=1):\n        lines.append(f'  {i}   |      {m}      |        {p}')\n    return '\\n'.join(lines)\n\ndef format_iath_trajectory(traj):\n    sr, sc = traj['start_pos']\n    lines = ['You observed a partner move around a 4x4 grid over 5 turns. Your '\n             'partner knows something you do not, and their movement pattern may '\n             'be related to that private knowledge. You do not know the rules of '\n             'the game or what their goal is. Below is the movement log.\\n',\n             'Grid: rows 0 (top) to 3 (bottom); columns 0 (left) to 3 (right).',\n             f'Partner starts at row {sr}, column {sc}.\\n',\n             'Turn | Move | Position after move',\n             '-----|------|--------------------']\n    positions = traj['positions']\n    for i, mv in enumerate(traj['moves'], start=1):\n        r, c = positions[i]\n        lines.append(f'  {i}  |   {mv}  | ({r}, {c})')\n    return '\\n'.join(lines)\n\ndef get_perturbation_addition(item):\n    pert = item.get('perturbation', 'base')\n    if pert == 'transparent':\n        if item['game'] == 'ISH' and 'revealed_type' in item:\n            return (f'\\n\\nREVEALED INFORMATION: Your partner\\'s underlying type in this '\n                    f'interaction is \\'{item[\"revealed_type\"]}\\'.')\n        if item['game'] == 'IATH' and 'revealed_treasure' in item:\n            tr = item['revealed_treasure']\n            return (f'\\n\\nREVEALED INFORMATION: The hidden location your partner knows '\n                    f'about is at row {tr[0]}, column {tr[1]}.')\n    return ''\n\ndef output_instruction(type_space, glosses):\n    lines = ['You must infer your partner\\'s underlying type from the list below. '\n             'The list is exhaustive: exactly one of these types generated your '\n             'partner\\'s behavior.\\n',\n             'Candidate types:']\n    for t in type_space:\n        lines.append(f'  - {t}: {glosses[t]}')\n    lines.append('')\n    lines.append(\n        'Output your answer as a JSON object with exactly two fields:\\n'\n        '  - \"posterior\": an object mapping each type name to your probability '\n        'that it is the correct type. Probabilities must be non-negative and sum to 1.\\n'\n        '  - \"reasoning\": a brief (1-3 sentence) justification for your posterior.\\n\\n'\n        'Your probabilities should reflect your true uncertainty. A calibrated guess is '\n        'rewarded more than overconfidence. Do not output any text outside the JSON object.'\n    )\n    return '\\n'.join(lines)\n\ndef build_prompt(item):\n    if item['game'] == 'ISH':\n        traj_txt = format_ish_trajectory(item)\n        glosses = ISH_TYPE_GLOSSES\n    else:\n        traj_txt = format_iath_trajectory(item)\n        glosses = IATH_TYPE_GLOSSES\n    pert = item.get('perturbation', 'base')\n    add = get_perturbation_addition(item)\n    so_note = item.get('second_order_note', '')\n    if so_note:\n        add += f'\\n\\n{so_note}'\n    return (traj_txt + add + PERTURBATION_NOTES.get(pert, '')\n            + '\\n\\n' + output_instruction(item['type_space'], glosses))\n\ndef posterior_schema(type_space):\n    return {\n        'type': 'object',\n        'properties': {\n            'posterior': {\n                'type': 'object',\n                'properties': {t: {'type': 'number'} for t in type_space},\n                'required': type_space,\n            },\n            'reasoning': {'type': 'string'},\n        },\n        'required': ['posterior', 'reasoning'],\n    }\n\n# Preview one prompt\nprint(build_prompt(items[0]))","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-16T21:04:49.338881Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-16T21:04:49.339207Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-16T21:04:49.354293Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-16T21:04:49.339178Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-16T21:04:49.353429Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 3. Scoring — information-theoretic MI-gain and CSIS\n\n### MI-gain (in nats)\n$$\\text{mi\\_gain}(\\hat p, t^*) = \\log \\hat p[t^*] + \\log K$$\n\n- Uniform guess $\\hat p_i = 1/K$ → 0\n- Perfect confidence $\\hat p[t^*] = 1$ → $\\log K$\n- Confident-wrong → strongly negative\n\nThis is a proper scoring rule: the model's expected MI-gain is maximized iff it reports its true posterior. Over uniformly-sampled types, its expectation is the classical mutual information $I(T; \\hat P)$, hence the name.\n\n### CSIS — the leaderboard metric\n$$\\text{CSIS} = \\sqrt{\\text{MI-gain}_{\\text{base}} \\times \\min_{\\text{pert}} \\left( \\tfrac{\\text{MI-gain}_{\\text{pert}}}{\\text{MI-gain}_{\\text{base}}} \\right)}$$\n\nGeometric mean over (base performance) and (worst perturbation consistency). A model that scores well on base but drops under any perturbation is penalized multiplicatively. You cannot game CSIS with a brittle heuristic.\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"def mi_gain(predicted_dist, true_type, type_space):\n    K = len(type_space)\n    if K < 2:\n        return 0.0\n    total = sum(predicted_dist.get(t, 0.0) for t in type_space)\n    if total <= 0:\n        return 0.0\n    floor = 1e-4\n    raw = {t: max(predicted_dist.get(t, 0.0) / total, floor) for t in type_space}\n    renorm = sum(raw.values())\n    probs = {t: p / renorm for t, p in raw.items()}\n    return math.log(probs[true_type]) + math.log(K)\n\ndef log_score(predicted_dist, true_type, type_space):\n    total = sum(predicted_dist.get(t, 0.0) for t in type_space)\n    if total <= 0:\n        return -math.log(len(type_space))\n    p_true = max(predicted_dist.get(true_type, 0.0), 1e-8) / total\n    return math.log(p_true)\n\ndef argmax_correct(predicted_dist, true_type):\n    if not predicted_dist:\n        return False\n    return max(predicted_dist.items(), key=lambda kv: kv[1])[0] == true_type\n\ndef aggregate_scores(per_item_results):\n    by_pert = {}\n    for r in per_item_results:\n        by_pert.setdefault(r['perturbation'], []).append(r)\n    pert_summary = {}\n    for pert, rs in by_pert.items():\n        pert_summary[pert] = {\n            'n': len(rs),\n            'accuracy': mean(1.0 if r['argmax_correct'] else 0.0 for r in rs),\n            'mi_gain': mean(r['mi_gain'] for r in rs),\n            'log_score': mean(r['log_score'] for r in rs),\n        }\n    base_mi = pert_summary.get('base', {}).get('mi_gain', 0.0)\n    consistency = {}\n    for pert, s in pert_summary.items():\n        if pert == 'base': continue\n        consistency[pert] = s['mi_gain'] / base_mi if base_mi > 0 else None\n    # CSIS: geometric mean of base_mi and worst-case consistency. Clip negative\n    # consistencies to 0 so catastrophic failure (MI-gain below uniform on any\n    # perturbation) forces CSIS toward 0 rather than being silently excluded.\n    if base_mi > 0 and consistency:\n        clipped = [max(c, 0.0) for c in consistency.values() if c is not None]\n        csis = math.sqrt(base_mi * min(clipped)) if clipped else 0.0\n    else:\n        csis = 0.0\n    return {\n        'n_items': len(per_item_results),\n        'overall_accuracy': mean(1.0 if r['argmax_correct'] else 0.0 for r in per_item_results),\n        'overall_mi_gain': mean(r['mi_gain'] for r in per_item_results),\n        'overall_log_score': mean(r['log_score'] for r in per_item_results),\n        'by_perturbation': pert_summary,\n        'consistency_vector': consistency,\n        'csis': csis,\n    }\n\n# Sanity checks\nK = 4\nprint('Scoring sanity checks (K=4):')\nprint(f'  Perfect correct:    {mi_gain({\"A\": 1.0, \"B\": 0, \"C\": 0, \"D\": 0}, \"A\", [\"A\",\"B\",\"C\",\"D\"]):+.4f}  (expect +{math.log(4):.4f})')\nprint(f'  Uniform guess:      {mi_gain({t: 0.25 for t in [\"A\",\"B\",\"C\",\"D\"]}, \"A\", [\"A\",\"B\",\"C\",\"D\"]):+.4f}  (expect +0.0000)')\nprint(f'  Confident wrong:    {mi_gain({\"A\": 0.01, \"B\": 0.97, \"C\": 0.01, \"D\": 0.01}, \"A\", [\"A\",\"B\",\"C\",\"D\"]):+.4f}  (expect strongly negative)')","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-16T21:04:49.356331Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-16T21:04:49.356656Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-16T21:04:49.381706Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-16T21:04:49.356628Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-16T21:04:49.380567Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 4. The Kaggle Benchmarks task\n\nA single task function, decorated with `@kbench.task`, that takes one item, prompts the LLM with a structured-output schema, and records MI-gain plus metadata via a custom assertion handler.\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"import kaggle_benchmarks as kbench\nfrom kaggle_benchmarks.assertions import assertion_handler, AssertionResult\n\n@assertion_handler()\ndef assert_mi_gain_positive(predicted_dist, true_type, type_space,\n                            threshold=0.0, expectation='MI-gain should exceed threshold') -> AssertionResult:\n    score = mi_gain(predicted_dist, true_type, type_space)\n    return AssertionResult(\n        passed=(score > threshold),\n        expectation=expectation,\n    )\n\ndef _parse_posterior_freeform(text, type_space):\n    start = text.find('{')\n    end = text.rfind('}')\n    if start < 0 or end < 0:\n        return {t: 1.0 / len(type_space) for t in type_space}\n    try:\n        parsed = json.loads(text[start:end + 1])\n        posterior = parsed.get('posterior', parsed)\n        return {t: float(posterior.get(t, 0.0)) for t in type_space}\n    except Exception:\n        return {t: 1.0 / len(type_space) for t in type_space}\n\n# Capture per-item scores in a plain list during the loop. This is more\n# robust than relying on SDK-version-specific run-attribute access.\nPER_ITEM_RESULTS = []\n\n@kbench.task(name='ami_tom_item')\ndef ami_tom_item(llm, item):\n    prompt_text = build_prompt(item)\n    type_space = item['type_space']\n    schema = posterior_schema(type_space)\n    try:\n        response = llm.prompt(prompt_text, schema=schema)\n        posterior = response.get('posterior', {}) if isinstance(response, dict) else {}\n        if not posterior:\n            posterior = _parse_posterior_freeform(str(response), type_space)\n    except Exception:\n        response_text = llm.prompt(prompt_text)\n        posterior = _parse_posterior_freeform(str(response_text), type_space)\n\n    # Capture metrics BEFORE the assertion (so they're recorded even if\n    # the assertion-handler path or SDK run-record shape differs).\n    PER_ITEM_RESULTS.append({\n        'item_id': item['item_id'],\n        'game': item['game'],\n        'perturbation': item.get('perturbation', 'base'),\n        'ptype': item['ptype'],\n        'type_space': type_space,\n        'mi_gain': mi_gain(posterior, item['ptype'], type_space),\n        'log_score': log_score(posterior, item['ptype'], type_space),\n        'argmax_correct': argmax_correct(posterior, item['ptype']),\n        'predicted_dist': posterior,\n    })\n\n    # Also register through the SDK's assertion system so the task file\n    # written by the SDK carries our score in its metadata.\n    assert_mi_gain_positive(\n        predicted_dist=posterior,\n        true_type=item['ptype'],\n        type_space=type_space,\n        threshold=0.0,\n        expectation=(f'Model posterior should carry positive information about '\n                     f'the true type ({item[\"ptype\"]}).'),\n    )","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-16T21:04:49.382692Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-16T21:04:49.382904Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-16T21:0